  <h2>Why Convert FLAC to MP3?</h2>
  <p>FLAC is a lossless format — it preserves every bit of the original recording. But that perfection comes at a cost: a typical 4-minute song in FLAC can be 30–40MB. The same song in MP3 at 320kbps is just 7–9MB.</p>
  <p>For everyday listening, streaming, sharing with friends, or uploading to platforms like Spotify or YouTube — MP3 is the practical choice. Most people genuinely cannot hear the difference between FLAC and a high-quality MP3.</p>

  <div class="compare-table-wrap">
